# Env vars for the real-Supabase acceptance lane (README.md § "Running the
# tests"). Nothing auto-loads this file — export them into your shell before
# `pnpm test`, e.g. `set -a; . ./.env; set +a`.

# Direct connection to your Supabase Postgres (service_role-capable).
# For the local dev stack, use the Postgres connection string from
# `supabase status` (port 54322 by default).
DATABASE_URL=postgres://postgres:postgres@localhost:54322/postgres

# The project's JWT secret (Settings → API → JWT Secret on hosted projects;
# `supabase status` → `JWT secret` for local dev). Used to sign HS256 JWTs
# exactly as GoTrue issues them. Keep it commented out until you have the real
# value: any value here — including an empty string — overrides the fixture JWT
# the hermetic lane falls back to in src/prisma/db.ts.
#SUPABASE_JWT_SECRET=

# Both vars enable the real-Supabase acceptance test
# (test/real-supabase.acceptance.test.ts); it is skipped when either is unset.
